Cell.Text: You have forsaken my gift. The ancient blood no longer flows through your veins. Don't deny it! | Count yourself fortunate that I'm a forgiving man. Now, be still while I give you the ancient blood once more.
[S] Good. Do not offend me by losing it again.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonNoVampiTopic2: I am ready to receive the ancient blood.

Cell.Text: G|You are a guest in this castle at my pleasure. I'll permit you to stay for now, but you're of no use to me like this.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonNoVampTopic3: I'm not ready yet. Give me more time.

Cell.Text: You have earned my trust, so I will share what I can.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonQuestionsTopic1: There are some things I want to ask you about.

Cell.Text: Serana and her mother disappeared long ago. | I commanded every vampire in the court to look for them, but after centuries of searching without success, I lost hope. | In my heart, I know that it was my wife, Valerica, who took my beloved daughter away from me. | If I ever see her again, she will pay most dearly for that betrayal.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonLore4Topic1: When you greeted Serana, it sounded like you hadn't seen her in a long time.

Cell.Text: What else do you want to know?
Her name was Valerica. She has been gone for so long now, I can only assume she has left this world, one way or another. | I will say only that we did not part on good terms.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonLore3Topic1: I heard you mention Serana's mother. What happened to her?

Cell.Text: I have not been mortal for many an age of this world. | So ancient is the kingdom that I ruled in my days as a living man, its name and its culture are lost to time, unknown to even the wisest scholars. | I could tell you the count in years, but it would mean nothing to you. | Let it suffice to say, you have not lived nearly long enough to comprehend time as I do.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonLore2Topic2: How long have you been a vampire?

Cell.Text: Because no vampire sired me. My blood is the pure blood, the first blood. | It was a gift bestowed to me by the daedra, and so has lost none of its potency. | That is all I will say for now. Perhaps if you earn my trust, I will reveal more.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonLore1Topic1: Why is your blood different from that of other vampires?

Cell.Text: You test my patience with these questions. | When you have earned the right to know the answers, I will give them to you.

Node.Caption: DLC1DialogueVampireBaseHarkonLore4Topic2: Why would your wife betray you?
